Johnson & Johnson submitted its Ottava robotic surgery platform to the FDA for authorization. headline: Connecticut Innovations Banks $41.0 Million in Venture Proceeds in Q2 FY26
summary: Connecticut Innovations (CI), Connecticut's strategic venture capital arm, today announced that it invested approximately $16.2 million in 23 companies and venture funds during the second quarter of its fiscal year, ending December 31, 2025. CI's investments leveraged $253.2 million in outside capital and generated $41 million in proceeds during the quarter. To date in fiscal year 2026, CI has invested $27.5 million and leveraged $340.1 million.
